<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1796" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1796">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.112C64/24.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 631.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-01">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that
                                Brigadier General Edwards has recently furnished the Legation with a
                                copy of the claims for damages against the Republic of Panama first
                                sent by him to the War Department on behalf of sixteen soldiers
                                wounded in the riot in the city of Panama on February 14 last. In
                                his report the War Department is requested by General Edwards to
                                present the claims to the Department of State for action thereon, in
                                view of which, and the fact of the considerable length of the
                                statements, I await the instructions of the Department before having
                                them recopied and forwarded, as I shall also await the Department’s
                                instructions regarding presentation of the claims to the Panaman
                                Government.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. Jennings Price.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>